During President Bush's visit to Iraq, a journalist threw shoes at him, symbolizing lingering hostility towards the war.
Despite the chaos, Bush remained calm, joking about the incident.
The shoe-throwing highlighted the mixed feelings in Iraq towards the man who toppled Saddam Hussein.
Bush emphasized progress in the war and the security agreement with Iraq.
The unexpected attack shocked aides and revealed a potential security breach.
The journalist, Muntadhar al-Zaidi, expressed his discontent by calling Bush a "dog" in Arabic.
This farewell gesture captured the complex emotions surrounding the Iraq war as Bush's presidency neared its end.
